<topic id='business_definition_measured_referral_to_treatment_period.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Measured Referral to Treatment Period - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_measured_referral_to_treatment_period">Measured Referral to Treatment Period</xref>
 is any 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_referral_to_treatment_period">REFERRAL TO TREATMENT PERIOD</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
It enables the time to the start of 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_first_definitive_treatment">First Definitive Treatment</xref>
 to be measured following a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service_request">SERVICE REQUEST</xref>
 to        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <p>
a 
                          <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_consultant_led_service">Consultant Led Service</xref>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>
an 
                          <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_interface_service">Interface Service</xref>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>
a 
                          <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_direct_access_service">Direct Access Service</xref>
 for Audiology                </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>
an 
                          <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_nhs_allied_health_professional_service__referral_to_treatment_measurement_">NHS Allied Health Professional Service (Referral To Treatment Measurement)</xref>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
See 
              <xref outputclass="attribute"
               keyref="attribute_referral_to_treatment_period_start_date">REFERRAL TO TREATMENT PERIOD START DATE</xref>
 for details of the types of 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service_request">SERVICE REQUEST</xref>
 which may start a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_referral_to_treatment_period">REFERRAL TO TREATMENT PERIOD</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
See 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_referral_to_treatment_period_included_in_referral_to_treatment_consultant-led_waiting_times_measurement">Referral To Treatment Period Included In Referral To Treatment Consultant-Led Waiting Times Measurement</xref>
 for the subset of 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_referral_to_treatment_period">REFERRAL TO TREATMENT PERIODS</xref>
 included in the Referral To Treatment Consultant-Led Waiting Times Measurement rules.        </p>
      <p>
Where a referral is made during a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_referral_to_treatment_period_excluded_from_target">Referral To Treatment Period Excluded From Target</xref>
 for the same disease, condition or injury and the referral is to a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_consultant_led_service">Consultant Led Service</xref>
 the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_referral_to_treatment_period_excluded_from_target">Referral To Treatment Period Excluded From Target</xref>
 will end with 
              <xref outputclass="attribute"
               keyref="attribute_referral_to_treatment_period_status">REFERRAL TO TREATMENT PERIOD STATUS</xref>
 of National Code 34 - 
              <i>Decision not to treat</i>
 and a new 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_referral_to_treatment_period">REFERRAL TO TREATMENT PERIOD</xref>
 will start.        </p>
  </div>
